## Task: Split Models/FileSystemModels.cs into per-DTO files
## Step: review

### Models/FileEntryDto.cs
```cs
using System;

namespace TestProject.Models;

/// <summary>
/// Represents a single file or directory entry returned from browsing or searching.
/// </summary>
public sealed record FileEntryDto(string Name, string Path, bool IsDirectory, long Size, DateTime LastModified, int ItemCount);

```
### Models/BrowseResultDto.cs
```cs
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;

namespace TestProject.Models;

/// <summary>
/// Represents the result of browsing a directory, including its contents and summary counts.
/// </summary>
public sealed record BrowseResultDto(string Path, string? Parent, IReadOnlyList<FileEntryDto> Entries, int FolderCount, int FileCount, long TotalSize);

```
### Models/SearchResultDto.cs
```cs
using System.Collections.Generic;

namespace TestProject.Models;

/// <summary>
/// Represents the result of a search query, containing matching file entries.
/// </summary>
public sealed record SearchResultDto(string Query, string Path, IReadOnlyList<FileEntryDto> Results);

```
### Models/MoveRequest.cs
```cs
namespace TestProject.Models;

/// <summary>
/// Represents a request to move a file or directory from one location to another.
/// </summary>
public sealed record MoveRequest(string SourcePath, string DestinationPath);

```
### Models/CopyRequest.cs
```cs
namespace TestProject.Models;

/// <summary>
/// Represents a request to copy a file or directory from one location to another.
/// </summary>
public sealed record CopyRequest(string SourcePath, string DestinationPath);

```
Split the flat `Models/FileSystemModels.cs` dumping ground (5 DTOs in one file) into focused per-DTO files. This resolves the name/file mismatch where the filename `FileSystemModels` doesn't describe any single type.

Create the following files under `Models/`, each containing exactly one type with its full XML doc comment (write fresh, concise doc comments — do NOT carry over temporal references):

1. `Models/FileEntryDto.cs` — `FileEntryDto` record.
2. `Models/BrowseResultDto.cs` — `BrowseResultDto` record.
3. `Models/SearchResultDto.cs` — `SearchResultDto` record.
4. `Models/MoveRequest.cs` — `MoveRequest` record.
5. `Models/CopyRequest.cs` — `CopyRequest` record.

All types stay in the `TestProject.Models` namespace. Delete `Models/FileSystemModels.cs` after creating the five files.

The existing record definitions are:
```csharp
public sealed record FileEntryDto(string Name, string Path, bool IsDirectory, long Size, System.DateTime LastModified, int ItemCount);
public sealed record BrowseResultDto(string Path, string? Parent, IReadOnlyList<FileEntryDto> Entries, int FolderCount, int FileCount, long TotalSize);
public sealed record SearchResultDto(string Query, string Path, IReadOnlyList<FileEntryDto> Results);
public sealed record MoveRequest(string SourcePath, string DestinationPath);
public sealed record CopyRequest(string SourcePath, string DestinationPath);
n```

Use `System.DateTime` (fully qualified) or add `using System;` per file as appropriate. Each file needs `namespace TestProject.Models;` (file-scoped namespace, matching the existing style).

No `using` changes are needed in any other file because the namespace `TestProject.Models` is unchanged.

Verification: Run `dotnet build TestProject.sln` and confirm compilation succeeds. Run `dotnet test TestProject.sln` and confirm all tests pass.

## Response Format (required)
Respond with ONLY a single valid JSON object matching the schema below.
- No prose, explanations, or commentary before or after the JSON.
- No markdown code fences (```), no headings — output the raw JSON object.
- Do NOT call any tools and do NOT end your turn on a thinking block. Emit the JSON object directly as text.

JSON schema:
{ approved: Whether the implementation is accepted, feedback: Detailed review feedback, issues: Array<{ file: File with the issue, description: What needs to be fixed, severity: "critical" | "minor" /* How important the fix is */ }> }

